## Guidelines for Specification

For each tile, pod, kit, and new LLC, provide:
- Primary function  
- Key features / embedded technologies  
- Main input sources  
- Material composition / manufacturing process  
- Estimated production cost & internal transfer / selling price  
- Revenue model & potential (internal use + retail/affiliate)  
- Project phase for rollout (prefer Phase 2: 2031–2035)  
- Integration notes (with RTK GPS Tiles, sensor nets, digital twins, etc.)  
- Viability & strategic rationale  

## Viability & Financial Targets

- Enable complete city services (energy resilience, indoor health, security, education, retail activation, industrial symbiosis)  
- Create new revenue streams: energy leasing, health/compliance services, retail signage/broadband, chemical/fuel sales  
- Target network-wide incremental revenue (mature): $6–$25B/year per major new industry  
- Payback period: 1–3 years per component/LLC  
- IRR uplift: +8–18% blended across additions  
- Prioritize low-regulatory-friction, high-closure synergies  

Output in clean, structured tables (one per category: Tiles, Pods, Kits, LLCs) followed by overall viability notes, prioritized LLC rollout order, and any cross-component integration synergies.

